  <title>SET MEMOBLOCK Command</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword>Commands</keyword>
    <keyword>Databases</keyword>
    <keyword>Memo files</keyword>
    <keyword>SET MEMOBLOCK command</keyword>
    <keyword>Setting<keyword>block size for memo files</keyword></keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">SET MEMOBLOCK Command</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><snippet src="__CommandInclude" inline="false"/></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading1">Purpose</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">Change the block size for memo files.</para>
    <para styleclass="Heading1">Syntax</para>
    <para styleclass="Code with box">SET MEMOBLOCK TO &lt;<text styleclass="Italic">nSize</text>&gt;</para>
    <para styleclass="Heading1">Description</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">The initial memo file block size depends on the RDD. &#160;For most drivers that support the .DBT memo file format, it is 512 bytes. &#160;However, if you are using BLOB files (.DBV) via inheritance from the DBFBLOB driver, the default is 1.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">SET MEMOBLOCK is functionally equivalent to calling RDDInfo(_SET_MEMOBLOCKSIZE, &lt;<text styleclass="Italic">nSize</text>&gt;). &#160;</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text"><snippet src="__IncludeLibRt" inline="false"/></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading1">See Also</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="html\M_XSharp_RT_Functions_RddInfo.htm" domain="XSharpRef.chm">RDDInfo()</link></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
  </body>
